HEADWORD: Adaptation
<hw>Ad`ap*ta"tion</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>adaptation</ets>, LL. <ets>adaptatio</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The act or process of adapting, or fitting; or the state of being
adapted or fitted; fitness.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Adaptation</xex> of the
means to the end.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Erskine.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The result of adapting; an adapted form.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Adaptative</ent>⟦br⟧
